Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.56,0:01:53.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Far away... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:02:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A long, long time ago... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.68,0:02:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There was a kindhearted man... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.43,0:02:13.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And a beautiful young woman{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.21,0:02:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Love was all they knew{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.10,0:02:36.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jean and Jeanne{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.37,0:02:44.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Happiness filled the air{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.66,0:02:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God smiled upon them{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.59,0:03:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}These two happy lovers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.31,0:03:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Jean and Jeanne{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.75,0:03:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They are united forever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.17,0:03:54.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}God smiled upon them{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:03:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Always, always together... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.77,0:04:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.32,0:04:08.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the story has just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.33,0:04:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baron, I am your faithful servant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wedding of Jean and Jeanne was not delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.41,0:04:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, it has already happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.64,0:04:28.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to ancient tradition,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.16,0:04:36.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the groom must pay you a marriage tax for the wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.35,0:05:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baron, this is money I raised by selling my cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.39,0:05:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.46,0:05:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please entrust me with Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.87,0:05:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cow? What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.21,0:05:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have only one cow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.80,0:05:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ten cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.05,0:05:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must give the equivalent of ten cows.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.64,0:05:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Please help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.12,0:05:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very poor. I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.85,0:05:33.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lady, please have mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.84,0:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, isn't this woman's belief impressive?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.25,0:05:40.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.43,0:05:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne is graceful and noble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.43,0:05:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most deserving of marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.75,0:05:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surely there isn't anything lustful about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.72,0:05:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's trustworthy and industrious. The villagers praise her highly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you love that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my Lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.62,0:06:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- And you?\N - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody, we've enjoyed a feast of cooked food.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.47,0:06:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's all eat dessert together!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.28,0:08:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jean...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.04,0:08:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's forget the past and start over.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.24,0:09:45.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the blue mirror, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.51,0:09:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is trembling?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.24,0:09:59.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not tears{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.69,0:10:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not a sigh{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.29,0:10:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's just that aftertaste that fades with time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.21,0:10:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or is it... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.04,0:10:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A woman's discouraged body?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.73,0:10:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the black dusk, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.81,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is weeping?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.87,0:11:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not the night wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.06,0:11:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not the crow{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.16,0:11:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's just that small peep of hope{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.18,0:11:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or is it... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.94,0:11:41.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A woman's painful moan?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.17,0:12:05.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't stare at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.81,0:12:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how tired he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.31,0:12:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.41,0:12:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.89,0:12:19.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have called me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.49,0:12:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.29,0:12:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I surely heard,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.75,0:12:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I need power!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.83,0:12:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I need someone to help me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what your heart is shouting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it also said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.47,0:12:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"If you help me, I'll give you anything."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.63,0:12:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Even my soul."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.60,0:12:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am... you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:57.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really a clown. What are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.82,0:13:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall serve you, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.49,0:13:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your wish is my command.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:06.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You? But you're so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.32,0:13:10.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.93,0:13:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can get much bigger,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.60,0:13:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and much, much stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.52,0:13:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all depends on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.90,0:13:38.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really are an odd one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.93,0:13:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See, I made you laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.56,0:13:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're happy at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.91,0:13:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... really did...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... smile...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.05,0:14:00.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I will ever smile again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.93,0:14:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.47,0:14:06.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have always been at your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.10,0:14:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know everything about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.81,0:14:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I am you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:16.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.96,0:14:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.76,0:14:36.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.85,0:15:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.52,0:15:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you go on like this, you'll die.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.54,0:15:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is useless to pray to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.56,0:15:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at your husband, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He truly is a hardworking man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.93,0:15:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who should follow God's will more than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.64,0:15:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already giving out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.81,0:15:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's going to get sick for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.59,0:15:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows if he'll even live to see the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.29,0:15:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.14,0:16:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.05,0:16:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.63,0:16:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except... I just want to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.67,0:16:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.80,0:16:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, without fail...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.74,0:16:40.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne took her fabric to the city to sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.46,0:16:46.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That year, there was a drought in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.97,0:16:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, the people had to continue paying heavy taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.12,0:16:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were desperate and downhearted, without the strength to resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.22,0:17:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Among them, only Jeanne had the strength to keep working.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the city...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.61,0:17:18.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne sold her fabric at a good price.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.32,0:17:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody wanted to bargain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only Jeanne and Jean had enough money to pay the high taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.19,0:17:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So people spread a rumor that she had made a deal with the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.55,0:17:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since Jean had paid the tax and pleased the authorities,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was appointed to be tax collector of the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.93,0:17:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once a poor farmer, Jean was now an outstanding officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:18:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at her husband in splendid uniform, Jeanne felt her heart soar.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.46,0:18:05.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Jeanne began to notice the villagers' attitudes changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.96,0:18:10.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The villagers felt uneasy around the two and began to avoid them intentionally.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.62,0:18:49.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the dark... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.00,0:18:53.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Burning... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.22,0:19:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the dark, burning... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Invite me in... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.78,0:19:28.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the dark, burning... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:47.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Burning hot... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.97,0:19:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the dark, burning... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.29,0:20:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the dark, burning... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.37,0:20:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.44,0:20:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.76,0:20:39.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.01,0:20:55.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Jeanne's agony had just begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.04,0:21:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,War had broken out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.51,0:21:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,War requires money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.09,0:21:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a war is won, it brings more wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.77,0:21:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You say that I am Lord here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.72,0:21:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,yet you collect very little money from the people!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... but... I can't give you any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.40,0:21:21.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! A drop of water can never move the mill!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:26.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't deliver the money in three days, you're finished!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.45,0:21:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Baron, the villagers have no money!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.23,0:21:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that you've forgotten your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.18,0:21:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To remind you, I'll cut off your left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.77,0:23:13.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be calling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.61,0:23:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You lied.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want strength?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.92,0:23:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're heartless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.31,0:23:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are mine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your body and your soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.06,0:23:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.09,0:23:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My soul belongs to Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.68,0:23:50.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's devoted to God and my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.93,0:23:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear, stupid girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.15,0:24:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you still argue with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.02,0:24:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I reconnect his hand for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.62,0:24:12.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband is already on the verge of ruin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.94,0:24:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.39,0:24:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, you are already mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.44,0:24:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to give you a chance to agree to this with your own free will.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.98,0:24:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your heart and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.85,0:24:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, that man will become...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.38,0:24:54.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My body, I will give you my lowly body.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.71,0:25:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will give it to you to save Jean...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.11,0:25:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, my heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.77,0:25:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and my soul... never!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.60,0:25:24.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good, now let me persuade you some more...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.34,0:26:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.75,0:27:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne put on a green robe and went into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.63,0:27:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Green is the color of the world's rulers,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.98,0:27:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so people call it "the Devil's color."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.42,0:27:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ordinarily, tax collectors don't need to borrow from money-lenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.53,0:27:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even the lender doesn't understand,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.90,0:28:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he has accepted Jeanne's offer, and lent her a large sum of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.15,0:28:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The money-lenders grumbling amongst themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.30,0:28:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"That woman must be possessed by the Devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.26,0:28:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In every era, men enjoy making war.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.98,0:28:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hunters, soldiers, and farmers unite, and all march away together.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.50,0:28:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The women are left with sad memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.26,0:28:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The men were gone for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A few years passed...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.19,0:29:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne became a money-lender herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.74,0:29:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She eventually grew to control the economy of her small village.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.22,0:29:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Court ladies and peasants alike came to fear and respect Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.24,0:29:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all too happy to please her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.95,0:29:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Baron would never allow it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.70,0:29:36.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's supposed to be in charge around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.86,0:29:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me or that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.96,0:29:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you, Mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.04,0:29:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.51,0:29:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress, you're always getting angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.11,0:29:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The war will continue for some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.57,0:29:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without that woman's strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.87,0:29:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we would be working in the castle's kitchen...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.89,0:29:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.48,0:29:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's possessed by the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.22,0:29:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.67,0:30:02.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, even though they had money and power,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.95,0:30:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jean was getting drunk every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.95,0:30:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, the army returned in triumph.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.37,0:30:30.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Feelings of joy and sorrow mixed as the women ran to greet the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.42,0:30:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of Jeanne made them uncomfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.06,0:30:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the army and women returned in triumph to the village square.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.34,0:30:57.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Jeanne showed up as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.94,0:31:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen that woman before...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.13,0:31:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baron, while you were gone, this country was turned upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.95,0:31:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.43,0:31:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman is possessed by the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.43,0:31:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil? That woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.27,0:31:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, people fear her more than anything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.90,0:31:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even more than you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.60,0:31:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.82,0:31:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.15,0:32:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil, go to Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.09,0:33:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the door! Save me! Husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.24,0:33:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.11,0:33:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody kill her.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.54,0:33:55.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let her suffer just by living.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.05,0:33:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a witch possessed by the Devil, that is best.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.39,0:34:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we should drive the Devil out as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.42,0:34:11.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the Devil will latch on to the soul he has possessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.64,0:34:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What can be done?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.67,0:34:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that woman is placed atop a pile of burning tinder,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.80,0:34:24.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,her soul will simply surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.01,0:34:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The flame of suffering should triumph over her pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.16,0:34:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's also possible that even though her body dies,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.43,0:34:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Devil himself could survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.21,0:34:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He could emerge from the flame and fly free.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.54,0:34:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What shall I do, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.73,0:34:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Lady, put her into a prison cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.36,0:34:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband has the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.00,0:35:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must constantly inflict severe punishment on her,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.09,0:35:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until she tells you she has a kind and chaste heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.94,0:35:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.44,0:35:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, bring that woman before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.54,0:36:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the black judgement, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.26,0:36:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is burning?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.21,0:36:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not a calm heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.41,0:36:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not repentance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.40,0:36:42.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's just that leftover trace of will power{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.12,0:36:48.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or is it... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:37:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A woman's bitterness revealed?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.31,0:37:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the white time, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.17,0:37:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is waiting?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.01,0:37:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not life's flame{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.33,0:37:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Not the grave{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.00,0:37:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's just that mirage in the heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.70,0:37:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or is it... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.49,0:38:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A woman's red blood flowing?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.44,0:40:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.05,0:40:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dear girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.83,0:40:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're at your wit's end. Even your husband has abandoned you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.99,0:40:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's too late, too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.92,0:40:53.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, I've been with you from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.69,0:40:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are my partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.55,0:41:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I, we are destined to be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.06,0:41:04.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is evil hidden deep in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.58,0:41:07.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And like a devil, you are seductive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.74,0:41:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you who made things like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.23,0:41:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Touch me, burn me...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.98,0:41:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since I am in Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.29,0:41:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.68,0:41:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The black hounds have bitten my flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.75,0:41:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.33,0:41:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your shiny teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.17,0:41:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thistles and thorns have stabbed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.57,0:41:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was also you!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.77,0:41:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The burn of those thorns.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.31,0:41:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.58,0:41:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I also made you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.11,0:41:37.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Made me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.48,0:41:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want an innocent, stupid soul...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.33,0:41:43.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that would sacrifice its own interests for the sake of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.21,0:41:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unleash your desperate fury.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.42,0:41:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold a hateful grudge against God.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.37,0:41:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A soul that will take revenge...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.73,0:41:55.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what I want most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.60,0:42:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're doing a good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.97,0:42:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're very beautiful today.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.19,0:42:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sight of your body, and your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.62,0:42:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They arouse my desire, and make me become the god of vengeance!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.31,0:42:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.25,0:42:36.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.33,0:42:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is your wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.12,0:42:46.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can give you anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.04,0:42:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.79,0:43:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do bad things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.62,0:43:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.12,0:43:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to do anything evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.27,0:43:18.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good answer! That's the real you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.68,0:43:21.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, give me...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.98,0:43:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the payment of your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.78,0:43:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to me freely as a gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.14,0:46:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the lonely wilderness, time slipped by.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.99,0:46:45.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Springtime came.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.97,0:46:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suddenly, Jeanne was no longer alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.47,0:46:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because she was communing with nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.17,0:46:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are very beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.65,0:47:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.13,0:47:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.48,0:47:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I belong in Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.10,0:47:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or is this Hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.73,0:47:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have sold myself to the Devil and I have no way out!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.01,0:47:23.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My hair should be the border of my hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.24,0:47:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My skin like that of an ugly frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.78,0:47:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My hatred burning like a pitch-black flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.01,0:47:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But no, that's not how I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.45,0:47:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have been deceived!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.18,0:47:43.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be a woman with incredible strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.80,0:47:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A woman everyone is afraid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.81,0:47:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But not like this. I don't want to forget about anger and hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.63,0:47:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anger, hatred, regret...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.23,0:47:56.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are not ugly things.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.96,0:48:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've become beautiful, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.38,0:48:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, just like falling in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.01,0:48:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lovely woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.37,0:48:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are more beautiful than God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.54,0:48:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nevertheless, a gloomy springtime arrived in the village.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.30,0:48:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jean had returned to his old life as a peasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.93,0:48:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even in this unchanging village,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.73,0:48:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a deadly, dark shadow was silently approaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.22,0:48:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bubonic plague.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.22,0:48:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1\fs20}The bubonic plague is the best-known variant of the deadly infectious disease caused by the enterobacteria Yersinia pestis. The infection in a human occurs when a person is bitten by a flea that has been infected by biting a rodent that itself has been infected by the bite of a flea carrying the disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.07,0:48:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deadly in almost every case.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.24,0:53:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already lit a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.35,0:53:24.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.64,0:53:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Jeanne, possessed by the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.59,0:53:31.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where... Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.29,0:53:34.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.19,0:53:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.47,0:53:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was carted off with the others while I was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.04,0:53:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still remember wanting to climb out desperately.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.71,0:53:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the first person I've seen after dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.59,0:53:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.48,0:53:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Giving you medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.88,0:53:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Liar! That's a poisonous flower!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.89,0:54:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes poison is medicine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.15,0:54:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to this, you can continue your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.60,0:54:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You trying to kill me?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.98,0:54:08.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you're already dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.13,0:54:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has he been cured?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.15,0:54:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did that happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.26,0:55:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Famine and plague are spreading!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.26,0:55:20.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}A famine is a widespread shortage of food that may apply to any faunal species.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.08,0:55:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The surviving villagers are all very hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.46,0:55:28.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a cottage that belongs to a witch.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.78,0:55:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every night, she causes an uproar.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.67,0:55:34.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a witch! She does the Devil's work!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.03,0:55:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows for sure, they feast on food and wine!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.13,0:55:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pig of a witch!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.52,0:57:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman... is still alive?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.81,1:02:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a colorful flower...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.53,1:02:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife was having a difficult, painful labor,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.98,1:02:38.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but after she drank juice from the flower, her fear was gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.83,1:02:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes, "Belladonna," which means beautiful woman...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.38,1:02:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what Jeanne said the flower was called.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.51,1:02:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we get another baby now, we won't be able to keep going!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.09,1:03:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, it's obvious my husband is trying hard not to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.44,1:03:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me feel so sorry for him.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.39,1:03:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm trying to figure out a way to make love without getting pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.04,1:03:17.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne told me,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.89,1:03:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should accept whatever hardships God gives to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.81,1:03:25.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is my fate.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.84,1:03:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, no matter how many hardships I'm faced with,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.94,1:03:31.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still find it very painful.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.41,1:03:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I can have a little happiness afterwards,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.44,1:03:42.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no regrets, no matter what I must suffer.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.48,1:03:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to see my grandson, who died in the war.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.32,1:03:56.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People say that Jeanne can bring people back from the dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.45,1:04:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After listening to my story, Jeanne shed many tears.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.20,1:04:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, she lets me smoke tobacco.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.20,1:04:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\i1}Tobacco is an product processed from the fresh leaves of plants in the genus Nicotiana.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.54,1:04:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She lets me drink all the red wine I want.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.29,1:04:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen your dead grandson yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.79,1:04:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.95,1:04:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard his voice?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.45,1:04:28.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.95,1:04:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she swindling you?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.31,1:04:34.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fell to my knees...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.35,1:04:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Praying and crying...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.68,1:04:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My body felt like fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.97,1:04:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it was all a dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.78,1:04:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I built up my courage, raised my head to have a look...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.65,1:04:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.79,1:05:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Hell itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.00,1:05:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was crying out loudly...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.88,1:05:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for my grandson.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.02,1:05:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you satisfied with this?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.53,1:05:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... I am very happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.97,1:05:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behold, it is betrayal against God.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.01,1:05:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's rebellion against the Baron!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.97,1:05:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman... burn her to death!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.43,1:05:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, that will be difficult. All the people support Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:51.03,1:05:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She has already escaped from the army.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.80,1:05:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you rule over this land?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.34,1:06:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy will show a weakness soon. Then we can defeat her.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.68,1:06:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me handle this!
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.24,1:07:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, little cutie?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.34,1:07:23.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to sleep with me?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.83,1:07:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, don't you recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.03,1:07:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mistress hates you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.55,1:07:38.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, I hate you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.54,1:07:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One day, I will be the one who kills you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.70,1:07:45.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.35,1:07:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because... I...
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.76,1:07:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love my mistress deeply.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.63,1:07:53.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.25,1:07:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, help me. Help me realize my dream.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.02,1:08:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be embraced by my mistress.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.66,1:08:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I am just a servant of humble origins.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.41,1:08:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She would never see someone of a lower class.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.94,1:08:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Different classes?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.06,1:08:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,God has assigned everyone his place.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.12,1:08:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To go against this is a betrayal against God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.40,1:08:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Devil's work.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:21.37,1:08:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to pursue my love, even if it means going to the Devil.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.53,1:08:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.49,1:08:31.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hurt me, witch!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.31,1:08:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.49,1:08:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.00,1:11:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That woman...
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.86,1:11:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The castle walls kept out the plague,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.83,1:12:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but they weren't able to keep out the curse of the witch.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.04,1:12:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baron, we must do something quickly.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.96,1:12:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go find her husband!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.74,1:12:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Husband!
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.70,1:12:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.44,1:12:39.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.26,1:13:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're unhappy aren't you, Jean?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.11,1:13:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:04.05,1:13:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can we just start over?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.61,1:13:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you stop doing these things?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.62,1:13:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Become an ordinary peasant's wife?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.01,1:13:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make a fresh start with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.40,1:13:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jean...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.87,1:13:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for abandoning you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.39,1:13:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- I was powerless to do anything then.\N- Don't say any more.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.93,1:13:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've already forgotten it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.18,1:13:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, please come back with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.21,1:13:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Back to the castle. \N- The castle?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.06,1:13:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Baron has already forgiven your mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.33,1:13:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, he admires your good deeds.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.75,1:13:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your work helping the sick and miserable.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.12,1:13:47.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've sacrificed yourself to solve the problems of others.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.11,1:13:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a very good person.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.13,1:13:54.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really believe that, Jean?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.42,1:13:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Baron wants to cooperate with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.43,1:14:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To cure the plague, relieve suffering.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.63,1:14:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With your knowledge and his power, many people could be saved.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.87,1:14:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Baron could have sent the army to catch you, or have you killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:16.14,1:14:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he doesn't want to do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.86,1:14:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that you know he is honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.78,1:14:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has promised me a piece of land and we can be happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.11,1:14:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And... if I refuse?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.62,1:14:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be killed, Jeanne!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.93,1:14:34.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Both you and me!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.95,1:14:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.25,1:14:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.96,1:16:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a trade, Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.09,1:16:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it allows us to work together toward...
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.05,1:16:59.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,making as many people as possible happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.07,1:17:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one hundred acres of fertile land is a sincere gift from me to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:09.17,1:17:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell us how to use this stinking flower.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.73,1:17:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:18.69,1:17:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you satisfied with one hundred acres?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.99,1:17:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.14,1:17:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, I'll let you rule over the village!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.92,1:17:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No wait, how about I make you the highest-ranked noble?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.10,1:17:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That should make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.37,1:17:37.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeanne, you're...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.90,1:17:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have the highest ranking of all nobles!
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.27,1:17:46.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else can I offer you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.43,1:17:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.90,1:17:51.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need any of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:53.81,1:17:57.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on earth do you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.05,1:17:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.96,1:18:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.57,1:18:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything in the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.97,1:18:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole world.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.68,1:18:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn her!
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.35,1:18:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burn this woman to death at once!
